<exercises xml:id="exercises-combinations">
<title>Exercises</title>

<exercisegroup xml:id="exercisegroup-combinations-compute" cols="2">
	<title>Evaluating the combination formula</title>
	<introduction><p>
		In each of <xref ref="exercisegroup-combinations-compute" text="type-local">Exercises</xref>,
		compute the value of the combination or formula of combinations.
		To obtain exact answers, you should simplify the factorial expressions before computing.
	</p></introduction>
	<exercise><p><m>\combination{4}{4}</m></p></exercise>
	<exercise><p><m>\combination{13}{5}</m></p></exercise>
	<exercise><p><m>\combination{1000000}{999998}</m></p></exercise>
	<exercise><p><m>\combination{7}{0}</m></p></exercise>
	<exercise><p><m>\combination{10}{6} \cdot \combination{6}{3}</m></p></exercise>
	<exercise><p><m>\combination{10}{9} / \combination{5}{2}</m></p></exercise>
</exercisegroup>

<exercisegroup xml:id="exercisegroup-combinations-verify" cols="2">
	<title>Combination formula identities</title>
	<introduction><p>
		In each of <xref ref="exercisegroup-combinations-verify" text="type-local">Exercises</xref>,
		verify the equality of combination formulas.
		Remember to consider the left-hand and right-hand sides of each equality <alert>separately</alert>,
		manipulating/simplifying one or the other or both sides until they are the same expression.
	</p></introduction>
	<exercise><p>
		<m>\displaystyle \combination{n}{k} = \frac{n}{k} \cdot \combination{n-1}{k-1}</m>
	</p></exercise>
	<exercise><p> <m>\displaystyle \combination{n}{k} = \frac{n}{n - k} \cdot \combination{n - 1}{k}</m> </p></exercise>
	<exercise><p> <m>\displaystyle \combination{n}{k} = \frac{n - k + 1}{k} \cdot \combination{n}{k - 1}</m> </p></exercise>
	<exercise><p>
		<m>\displaystyle \combination{n + k}{n} = \combination{n + k}{k}</m>
	</p></exercise>
</exercisegroup>

<exercise><p>
	Choose a value for <m>m</m> so that the equality in <xref ref="proposition-combinations-extram-comb-formula" />
	becomes a formula for the sum <m>1 + 2 + 3 + \dotsb + n</m>.
</p></exercise>

</exercises>
